Mechanism: The jbFileSync function in justbash-filesync starts a polling loop (every ~600 ms) that watches /notebook/*.js files in the in-memory filesystem for lastModified timestamp changes. When a change is detected, the file text is dynamically imported via window.importShim into a blob URL, producing a define() function; jbApply then parses that function (via probeDefine) to extract each cell's name, pid, and dependencies, diffs them against the live Observable runtime variables, and applies the adds/updates/removes so the running notebook reflects the file. When the agent's own write_file or edit_file tools change a /src/ file directly, the hostbridge's applyModuleFile does the same import-apply cycle immediately (without waiting for the poll loop), and re-exports the canonical form back to /notebook/.
